text.tspan: Fertility rate vs. GDP per capita, 1950 to 2019

The
total fertility rate
summarizes the total number of births a woman would have, if she experienced the birth
rates seen in women of each age group in one particular year across her childbearing years. This is shown
against gross domestic product (GDP) per capita, adjusted for inflation and for differences in living costs
Births per woman (live births per woman)
Data source: UN, World Population Prospects (2024); Feenstra et al. (2015), Penn World Table (2021)
